edge and add their names to the matriculation book  Also at this time  new cadets receive room assignments  mailbox numbers  email addresses  and Reserve Office Training Corps  ROTC  information   New cadets who attended the Summer Transition Program should bring all uniform items issued to them  New cadets who did not attend the Summer Transition Program will be issued athletic uniforms at Matriculation in Cameron Hall  New cadets whose last last name begins with  A L report to Cameron Hall 7 30 a m    9 00 a m  M Z report to Cameron Hall  9 00   11 30 a m    Matriculation Events7 30 a m    11 30 a m  Matriculation 8 00 a m  1 p m Matriculation Fair 2 00 p m  Superintendent s Welcome 2 30 p m   approximately  March Off 3 00 p m  Finish Get the details   For ParentsInformation about mail  phone calls  check cashing  the bookstore  and photostore  For Parents   Families   New Cadet Oath CeremonyNew Cadets will take a historic tour and recite the Cadet Oath before they charge across the battlefield exactly as the New Market cadets did on May 15  1864  More about the Oath   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 